{"en":[{"id":"27459835","caption_id":"128569","seq":"1","text":"There are 196 countries in the world today and virtually none of them have purple on their national flag.","translate_comment":"","start":"9.88","dur":"5.809","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459836","caption_id":"128569","seq":"2","text":"Throughout history, purple was never used to represent a kingdom, civilization, or Empire.","translate_comment":"","start":"16.34","dur":"5.07","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459837","caption_id":"128569","seq":"3","text":"So what's wrong with purple?","translate_comment":"","start":"21.98","dur":"1.549","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459838","caption_id":"128569","seq":"4","text":"It's such a popular color today.","translate_comment":"","start":"23.87","dur":"1.89","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459839","caption_id":"128569","seq":"5","text":"Why would no country use it in their flag?","translate_comment":"","start":"26.24","dur":"2.25","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459840","caption_id":"128569","seq":"6","text":"The answer is really quite simple.","translate_comment":"","start":"29.65","dur":"2.09","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459841","caption_id":"128569","seq":"7","text":"Purple was just far too expensive.","translate_comment":"","start":"32.429","dur":"2.24","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459842","caption_id":"128569","seq":"8","text":"No countries have purple on their flag because up until the 1800s, purple was worth more than its weight in gold.","translate_comment":"","start":"35.279","dur":"6.881","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459843","caption_id":"128569","seq":"9","text":"The color purple has been associated with royalty power and wealth for centuries.","translate_comment":"","start":"43.18","dur":"4.12","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459844","caption_id":"128569","seq":"10","text":"In fact, Queen Elizabeth I forbade anyone except close members of the royal family to wear it.","translate_comment":"","start":"47.509","dur":"6.151","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459845","caption_id":"128569","seq":"11","text":"Purple's elite status stems from the rarity and cost of the dye originally used to produce it.","translate_comment":"","start":"54.4","dur":"5.2","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459846","caption_id":"128569","seq":"12","text":"The dye initially used to make purple came from the Phoenician trading city of Tyre, which is now in modern-day Lebanon.","translate_comment":"","start":"60.17","dur":"6.83","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459847","caption_id":"128569","seq":"13","text":"Fabric traders obtained the dye from a small sea snail that was only found in the Tyre region of the Mediterranean.","translate_comment":"","start":"67.69","dur":"6.22","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459848","caption_id":"128569","seq":"14","text":"A lot of work went into producing the dye as more than 10,000 snails were needed to create just one gram of tyrian purple.","translate_comment":"","start":"74.69","dur":"8.56","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459849","caption_id":"128569","seq":"15","text":"Since only wealthy rulers could afford to buy and wear the color, it became associated with the Imperial classes of Rome, Egypt, and Persia.","translate_comment":"","start":"83.929","dur":"7.791","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459850","caption_id":"128569","seq":"16","text":"Purple also came to represent spirituality and holiness because the ancient Emperor's kings and queens that wore the color were often thought of as gods or descendants of the gods.","translate_comment":"","start":"92.83","dur":"10.74","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459851","caption_id":"128569","seq":"17","text":"Sometimes, however, the dye was too expensive even for royalty.","translate_comment":"","start":"104.21","dur":"4.59","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459852","caption_id":"128569","seq":"18","text":"Third century Roman Emperor Aurelio famously wouldn't allow his wife to buy a shawl made from tyrian purple silk because it literally cost three times its weight in gold.","translate_comment":"","start":"108.93","dur":"10.87","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459853","caption_id":"128569","seq":"19","text":"A single pound of dye cost three pounds of gold, which is the equivalent of fifty six thousand dollars today.","translate_comment":"","start":"120.52","dur":"6.75","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459854","caption_id":"128569","seq":"20","text":"So since the sheer price of purple was so astronomically high, no one not even the richest nations could afford to have purple on their flag.","translate_comment":"","start":"128.94","dur":"8.03","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459855","caption_id":"128569","seq":"21","text":"The hue became more accessible to lower-class is about a century and a half ago.","translate_comment":"","start":"137.63","dur":"4.12","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459856","caption_id":"128569","seq":"22","text":"In 1856, 18-year old English chemist William Henry Perkin accidentally created a synthetic purple compound while attempting to synthesize quinine an anti-malaria drug.","translate_comment":"","start":"142.309","dur":"12.43","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459857","caption_id":"128569","seq":"23","text":"He noticed that the compound could be used to dye fabrics, so he patented the dye, manufactured it and got filthy rich.","translate_comment":"","start":"155.28","dur":"8.14","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459858","caption_id":"128569","seq":"24","text":"Purple dye was then mass-produced so just about everybody could afford it.","translate_comment":"","start":"164.61","dur":"3.71","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459859","caption_id":"128569","seq":"25","text":"The elite stopped valuing purple and the status symbol faded away but the country flags remain the same.","translate_comment":"","start":"168.76","dur":"6.14","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459860","caption_id":"128569","seq":"26","text":"Since 1900, a handful of new national flags have been designed and a few of them have opted to use purple in their flag.","translate_comment":"","start":"175.37","dur":"6.56","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459861","caption_id":"128569","seq":"27","text":"So don't be making any bets just yet.","translate_comment":"","start":"182.19","dur":"2.41","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459862","caption_id":"128569","seq":"28","text":"Hopefully you found this interesting.","translate_comment":"","start":"185.28","dur":"1.68","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459863","caption_id":"128569","seq":"29","text":"Sometimes the simplest questions have the most fascinating answers.","translate_comment":"","start":"187.41","dur":"3.759","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null},{"id":"27459864","caption_id":"128569","seq":"30","text":"For more interesting videos like this one, please subscribe.","translate_comment":"","start":"192.24","dur":"3.46","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522135159","updated_at":null}],"zh-Hant":[{"id":"27707708","caption_id":"128570","seq":"1","text":"\u4e16\u754c\u4e0a\u5171\u6709 196 \u500b\u570b\u5bb6\uff0c\u537b\u6c92\u6709\u4efb\u4f55\u4e00\u500b\u570b\u5bb6\u570b\u65d7\u4f7f\u7528\u7d2b\u8272","translate_comment":"","start":"9.88","dur":"5.809","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522292447","updated_at":null},{"id":"27707709","caption_id":"128570","seq":"2","text":"\u7e31\u89c0\u6b77\u53f2\uff0c\u5f9e\u4f86\u6c92\u6709\u4e00\u500b\u570b\u5bb6\u3001\u6587\u660e\uff0c\u6216\u5e1d\u570b\u4f7f\u7528\u7d2b\u8272\u4f5c\u70ba\u4ee3\u8868","translate_comment":"","start":"16.34","dur":"5.07","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522292447","updated_at":null},{"id":"27707710","caption_id":"128570","seq":"3","text":"\u7d2b\u8272\u6709\u4ec0\u9ebc\u554f\u984c\u55ce\uff1f","translate_comment":"","start":"21.98","dur":"1.549","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522292447","updated_at":null},{"id":"27707711","caption_id":"128570","seq":"4","text":"\u7d2b\u8272\u5728\u73fe\u4eca\u975e\u5e38\u53d7\u6b61\u8fce","translate_comment":"","start":"23.87","dur":"1.89","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522292447","updated_at":null},{"id":"27707712","caption_id":"128570","seq":"5","text":"\u90a3\u70ba\u4ec0\u9ebc\u6c92\u6709\u570b\u5bb6\u5c07\u5b83\u7528\u5728\u570b\u65d7\u4e0a\u5462\uff1f","translate_comment":"","start":"26.24","dur":"2.25","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522292447","updated_at":null},{"id":"27707713","caption_id":"128570","seq":"6","text":"\u9019\u500b\u7b54\u6848\u5176\u5be6\u975e\u5e38\u7c21\u55ae","translate_comment":"","start":"29.65","dur":"2.09","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522292447","updated_at":null},{"id":"27707714","caption_id":"128570","seq":"7","text":"\u7d2b\u8272\u592a\u8cb4\u4e86","translate_comment":"","start":"32.429","dur":"2.24","is_scores":null,"created_at":"1522292447","updated_at":null},{"id":"27707715","caption_id":"128570","seq":"8","text":"\u6c92\u6709\u570b\u5bb6\u5728\u570b\u65d7\u4e0a\u4f7f\u7528\u7d2b\u8272\u662f\u